  "text": "located in chromosome 16 (chr16), and 2 genes in chr1, whereas the remaining five genes mapped to five different chromosomes ( Figure 1 and Table 2 ). In chr19, the NCOA6 gene overlapped with ASIP in 19q12, and their relative order was resolved by interphase FISH using BMP7 as the second reference marker. The order of the three genes was revealed as cen-ASIP-NCOA6-BMP7-tel ( Figure 1F , far right). Location of CTNNB1, DAB2IP, and SOX9 in chr17, chr4 and chr16, respectively, was confirmed by co-hybridized reference markers. No genes were assigned to chromosome arms that previously did not have a mapped marker. No discrepancies of the known conserved synteny blocks between camelids, cattle and human [CITATION_1] were observed.",
